{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Hebrews

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Christ the Mediator

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}God, who, of old, at many times and in many ways, spoke to our ancestors, by the prophets,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}has in these latter days spoken to us by the Son, whom he appointed the heir of all things, and through whom he made the universe.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}For he is the radiance of the glory of God and the expression of his being, upholding all creation by the power of his word; and, when he had made an expiation for the sins of humanity, he took his seat at the right hand of God\uc1\u8217*s Majesty on high,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}having shown himself as much greater than the angels as the name that he has inherited surpasses theirs.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}For to which of the angels did God ever say \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You are my Son; this day I have become your Father\uc1\u8221*?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
or again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will be to him a Father, and he will be to me a Son\uc1\u8221*?
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And again, when God brought the firstborn into the world, he said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Let all the angels of God bow down before him.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Speaking of the angels, he said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*He makes the winds his angels
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and the flames of fire his servants\uc1\u8221*;
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}while of the Son he said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*God is your throne for ever and ever;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
the sceptre of his kingdom is the sceptre of Justice;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}You love righteousness and hates iniquity;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
therefore God, your God, has anointed you with the festal oil more abundantly than your peers.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You, Lord, in the beginning did lay the foundation of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and the heavens are the work of your hands.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}They will perish, but you remain;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
as a garment they will all grow old;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}As a mantle you will fold them up,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and as a garment they will be changed,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
but you are the same, and your years will know no end.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}To which of the angels has God ever said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Sit you at my right hand
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
until I put your enemies as a stool for your feet\uc1\u8221*?
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Are not all the angels spirits in the service of God, sent out to minister for the sake of those who are destined to obtain salvation?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}Therefore we must give still more heed to what we were taught, so we do not drift away.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}For, if the message which was delivered by angels had its authority confirmed, so that every offence against it, or neglect of it, met with a fitting requital,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}how can we, of all people, expect to escape, if we disregard so great a salvation? It was the Master who at the outset spoke of this salvation, and its authority was confirmed for us by those who heard him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}while God himself added his testimony to it by signs, and marvels, and many different miracles, as well as by imparting the Holy Spirit as he saw fit.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}God has not given to angels the control of that future world of which we are speaking!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}No; a writer has declared somewhere \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*What are mere mortals that you should remember them?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
Or human beings that you should care for them?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}You have made them, for a while, lower than angels;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
with glory and honour you have crowned them;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
you have set them over all that your hands have made;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}you have placed all things beneath their feet.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
This \uc1\u8220*placing of everything\uc1\u8221* under humanity means that there was nothing which was not placed under them. As yet, however, we do not see everything placed under humanity.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}What our eyes do see is Jesus, who was made for a while lower than angels, now, because of his sufferings and death, crowned with glory and honour; so that his tasting the bitterness of death should, in God\uc1\u8217*s loving kindness, be on behalf of all humanity.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}It was, indeed, fitting that God, for whom and through whom all things exist, should, when leading many children to glory, make the author of their salvation perfect through suffering.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}For he who purifies, and those whom he purifies, all spring from One; and therefore he is not ashamed to call them his brothers and sisters.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}He says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will tell of your name to my brothers and sisters,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
in the midst of the congregation I will sing your praise.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*As for me, I will put my trust in God.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
And yet again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*See, here am I and the children whom God gave me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Therefore, since human nature is the common heritage of the children, Jesus also shared it, in order that by death he might render powerless him whose power lies in death \uc1\u8211* that is, the devil \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and so might deliver all those who, from fear of death, had all their lives been living in slavery.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}It was not, surely, to the help of the angels that Jesus came, but to the help of the descendants of Abraham.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And consequently it was necessary that he should in all points be made like his brothers and sisters, in order that he might prove a merciful as well as a faithful high priest in humanity\uc1\u8217*s relations with God, for the purpose of expiating the sins of his people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}The fact that he himself suffered under temptation enables him to help those who are tempted.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}Therefore, my Christian friends, you who, all alike, have received the call from heaven, fix your attention on Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our religion.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}See how faithful he was to the God who appointed him, as Moses was in the whole house of God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}He has been deemed worthy of far higher honour than Moses, just as the founder of the house is held in greater regard than the house itself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For every house has its founder, and the founder of the universe is God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}While the faithful service of Moses in the whole house of God was that of a servant, whose duty was to bear testimony to a message still to come,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}the faithfulness of Christ was that of a son set over the house of God. And we are his house \uc1\u8211* if only we retain, unshaken to the end, the courage and confidence inspired by our hope.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore, as the Holy Spirit says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*If today you hear God\uc1\u8217*s voice,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}harden not your hearts, as when Israel provoked me
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
on the day when they tried my patience in the desert,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Where your ancestors tried my forbearance,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
and saw my mighty deeds for forty years.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Therefore I was sorely vexed with that generation,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
and I said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Their hearts are always straying;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
they have never learned my ways\uc1\u8217*;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}While in my wrath I swore \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
\uc1\u8216*They will never enter upon my rest.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Be careful, friends, that there is never found in anyone of you a wicked and faithless heart, shown by that person separating themselves from the living God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Rather encourage one another daily \uc1\u8211* while there is a today \uc1\u8211* to prevent anyone among you from being hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For we now all share in the Christ, if indeed we retain, unshaken to the end, the confidence that we had at the first.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}To use the words of scripture \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*If today you hear God\uc1\u8217*s voice,
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
harden not your hearts, as when Israel provoked me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Who were they who heard God speak and yet provoked him? Were not they all those who left Egypt under the leadership of Moses?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And with whom was it that God was sorely vexed for forty years? Was not it with those who had sinned, and who fell dead in the desert?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And who were they to whom God swore that they should not enter upon his rest, if not those who had proved faithless?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}We see, then, that they failed to enter upon it because of their want of faith.{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}We must, therefore, be very careful, though there is a promise still standing that we will enter upon God\uc1\u8217*s rest, that none of you even appear to have missed it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}For we have had the good news told us just as they had. But the message which they heard did them no good, since they did not share the faith of those who were attentive to it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Upon that rest we who have believed are now entering. As God has said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*In my wrath I swore \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2080\li2800
\uc1\u8216*They will never enter upon my rest;\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
Although God\uc1\u8217*s work was finished at the creation of the world;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}for, in a passage referring to the seventh day, you will find these words \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*God rested on the seventh day after all his work.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}On the other hand, we read in that passage \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*They will never enter upon my rest.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Since, then, there is still a promise that some will enter upon this rest, and since those who were first told the good news did not enter upon it, because of their disbelief,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}again God fixed a day. \uc1\u8220*Today,\uc1\u8221* he said, speaking after a long interval through the mouth of David, in the passage already quoted \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*If today you hear God\uc1\u8217*s voice
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
harden not your hearts.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Now if Joshua had given \uc1\u8220*rest\uc1\u8221* to the people, God would not have spoken of another and later day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}There is, then, a Sabbath rest still awaiting God\uc1\u8217*s people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For the person who enters upon God\uc1\u8217*s rest do themselves rest after their work, just as God did.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Let us, therefore, make every effort to enter upon that rest, so that none of us fall through such disbelief as that of which we have had an example.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}God\uc1\u8217*s message is a living and active power, sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing its way until it penetrates soul and spirit \uc1\u8211* not the joints only but the marrow \uc1\u8211* and detecting the inmost thoughts and purposes of the mind.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}There is no created thing that can hide itself from the sight of God. Everything is exposed and laid bare before the eyes of him to whom we have to give account.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}We have, then, in Jesus, the Son of God, a great high priest who has passed into the highest heaven; let us, therefore, hold fast to the faith which we have professed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Our high priest is not one unable to sympathise with our weaknesses, but one who has in every way been tempted, exactly as we have been, but without sinning.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Therefore, let us draw near boldly to the throne of love, to find pity and love for the hour of need.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5}Every high priest, taken from among the people, is appointed as their representative in their relations with God, to offer both gifts and sacrifices in expiation of sins.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And he is able to sympathise with the ignorant and deluded, since he is himself subject to weakness,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and is therefore bound to offer sacrifices for sins, not only for the people, but equally so for himself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Nor does anyone take that high office on themselves, until they have been called to do so by God, as Aaron was.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}In the same way, even the Christ did not take the honour of the high priesthood on himself, but he was appointed by him who said to him \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You are my Son; this day I have become your Father\uc1\u8221*;
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}and on another occasion also \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You are a priest for all time of the order of Melchizedek.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Jesus, in the days of his earthly life, offered prayers and supplications, with earnest cries and with tears, to him who was able to save him from death; and he was heard because of his devout submission.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Son though he was, he learned obedience from his sufferings;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}and, being made perfect, he became to all those who obey him the source of eternal salvation,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}while God himself pronounced him a high priest of the order of Melchizedek.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Now on this subject I have much to say, but it is difficult to explain it to you, because you have shown yourselves so slow to learn.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}For whereas, considering the time that has elapsed, you ought to be teaching others, you still need someone to teach you the alphabet of the divine revelation, and need again to be fed with milk instead of with \uc1\u8220*solid food.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}For everyone who still has to take milk knows nothing of the teaching of righteousness; they are a mere infant.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But solid food is for Christians of mature faith \uc1\u8211* those whose faculties have been trained by practice to distinguish right from wrong.{\cf1\f1\fs22 6}Therefore, let us leave behind the elementary teaching about the Christ and press on to perfection, not always laying over again a foundation of repentance for a lifeless formality, of faith in God \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}teaching concerning baptisms and the laying on of hands, the resurrection of the dead and a final judgment.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Yes and, with God\uc1\u8217*s help, we will.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}For if those who were once for all brought into the light, and learned to appreciate the gift from heaven, and came to share in the Holy Spirit,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}and learned to appreciate the beauty of the divine message, and the new powers of the coming age \uc1\u8211*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}if those, I say, fell away, it would be impossible to bring them again to repentance; they would be crucifying the Son of God over again for themselves, and exposing him to open contempt.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Ground that drinks in the showers that from time to time fall on it, and produces vegetation useful to those for whom it is tilled, receives a blessing from God;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}but, if it bears thorns and thistles, it is regarded as worthless, it is in danger of being cursed, and its end will be the fire.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But about you, dear friends, even though we speak in this way, we are confident of better things \uc1\u8211* of things that point to your salvation.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}For God is not unjust; he will not forget the work that you did, and the love that you showed for his name, in sending help to your fellow Christians \uc1\u8211* as you are still doing.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But our great desire is that every one of you should be equally earnest to attain to a full conviction that our hope will be fulfilled, and that you should keep that hope to the end.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Then you will not show yourselves slow to learn, but you will copy those who, through faith and patience, are now entering upon the enjoyment of God\uc1\u8217*s promises.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}When God gave his promise to Abraham, since there was no one greater by whom he could swear, he swore by himself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}His words were \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will assuredly bless you and increase your numbers.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And so, after patiently waiting, Abraham obtained the fulfilment of God\uc1\u8217*s promise.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}People, of course, swear by what is greater than themselves, and with them an oath is accepted as putting a matter beyond all dispute.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And therefore God, in his desire to show, with unmistakable plainness, to those who were to enter on the enjoyment of what he had promised, the unchangeableness of his purpose, bound himself with an oath.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}For he intended us to find great encouragement in these two unchangeable things, which make it impossible for God to prove false \uc1\u8211* we, I mean, who fled for safety where we might lay hold on the hope set before us.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}This hope is an anchor for our souls, secure and strong, and it reaches into the sanctuary that lies behind the curtain,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}where Jesus, our forerunner, has entered on our behalf, after being made for all time a high priest of the order of Melchizedek.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Paramount Priesthood of the Christ

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 7}It was this Melchizedek, king of Salem and priest of the Most High God, who met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings, and gave him his blessing;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and it was to him that Abraham allotted a tithe of all the spoil. The meaning of his name is \uc1\u8220*king of righteousness,\uc1\u8221* and besides that, he was also king of Salem, which means \uc1\u8220*king of peace.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}There is no record of his father, or mother, or lineage, nor again of any beginning of his days, or end of his life. In this he resembles the Son of God, and stands before us as a priest whose priesthood is continuous.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Consider, then the importance of this Melchizedek, to whom even the patriarch Abraham himself gave a tithe of the choicest spoils.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Those descendants of Levi, who are from time to time appointed to the priesthood, are directed to collect tithes from the people in accordance with the Law \uc1\u8211* that is from their own kindred, although they also are descended from Abraham.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But Melchizedek, although not of this lineage, received tithes from Abraham, and gave his blessing to the man who had God\uc1\u8217*s promises.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Now no one can dispute that it is the superior who blesses the inferior.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}In the one case the tithes are received by people who are mortal; in the other case by one about whom there is the statement that his life still continues.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Moreover, in a sense, even Levi, who is the receiver of the tithes, has, through Abraham, paid tithes;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}for Levi was still in the body of his ancestor when Melchizedek met Abraham.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}If, then, perfection had been attainable through the Levitical priesthood \uc1\u8211* and it was under this priesthood that the people received the Law \uc1\u8211* why was it still necessary that a priest of a different order should appear, a priest of the order of Melchizedek and not of the order of Aaron?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}With the change of the priesthood a change of the Law became a necessity.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And he of whom all this is said belonged to quite a different tribe, no member of which has ever served at the altar.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}For it is plain that our Lord had sprung from the tribe of Judah, though of that tribe Moses said nothing about their being priests.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}All this becomes even yet plainer when we remember that a new priest has appeared, resembling Melchizedek,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}and that he was appointed, not under a Law regulating only earthly matters, but by virtue of a life beyond the reach of death;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}for that is the meaning of the declaration \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You are for all time a priest of the order of Melchizedek.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}On the one hand, we have the abolition of a previous regulation as being both inefficient and useless{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}(for the Law never brought anything to perfection); and, on the other hand, we have the introduction of a better hope, which enables us to draw near to God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Then again, the appointment of this new priest was ratified by an oath, which is not so with the Levitical priests,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}but his appointment was ratified by an oath, when God said to him \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*The Lord has sworn, and will not change, \uc1\u8216*You are a priest for all time.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And the oath shows the corresponding superiority of the covenant of which Jesus is appointed the surety.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Again, new Levitical priests are continually being appointed, because death prevents their remaining in office;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}but Jesus remains for all time, and therefore the priesthood that he holds will never pass to another.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And that is why he is able to save perfectly those who come to God through him, living for ever, as he does, to intercede of their behalf.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}This was the high priest that we needed \uc1\u8211* holy, innocent, spotless, withdrawn from sinners, exalted above the highest heaven,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}one who has no need to offer sacrifices daily as those high priests have, first for their own sins, and then for those of the people. For this he did once and for all, when he offered himself as the sacrifice.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}The Law appoints as high priests men who are weak, but the words of God\uc1\u8217*s oath, which was later than the Law, name the Son as, for all time, the perfect priest.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 8}To sum up what I have been saying: Such is the high priest that we have, one who has taken his seat at the right hand of the throne of God\uc1\u8217*s Majesty in heaven,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}where he serves in the sanctuary, in that true tent set up by the Lord and not by man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Every high priest is appointed for the purpose of offering gifts and sacrifices to God; it follows, therefore, that this high priest must have some offering to make.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}If he were, however, still on earth, he would not even be a priest, since there are already priests who offer the gifts as the Law directs.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}(These priests, it is true, are engaged in a service which is only a copy and shadow of the heavenly realities, as is shown by the directions given to Moses when he was about to construct the tent. \uc1\u8220*Look to it,\uc1\u8221* are the words, \uc1\u8220*that you make every part in accordance with the pattern shown you on the mountain.\uc1\u8221*){\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But Jesus, as we see, has obtained a ministry as far excelling theirs, as the covenant of which he is the intermediary, based, as it is, on better promises, excels the former covenant.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}If that first covenant had been faultless, there would have been no occasion for a second.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}But, finding fault with the people, God says \uc1\u8211*
